# Base URL (no trailing slash, no /predict) of the Node backend this app
# talks to. Expo only exposes env vars prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to app code.
#
# - Android emulator: 10.0.2.2 is a special alias the emulator provides for
#   your host machine's localhost, so this works out of the box with no .env
#   at all if your backend runs on your dev machine on port 3000.
# - iOS simulator: localhost works directly since the simulator shares your
#   machine's network stack.
# - Real physical device (Android or iOS): neither of the above will work.
#   Find your machine's LAN IP (e.g. `ipconfig` on Windows, `ifconfig`/`ip a`
#   on macOS/Linux) and set it below, e.g. http://192.168.1.5:3000. Your
#   phone and dev machine must be on the same network.
EXPO_PUBLIC_ANDROIDAPI=http://10.0.2.2:3000
EXPO_PUBLIC_IOSAPI=http://localhost:3000
